Package Alicisindan

Class Listing

  • java.lang.Object
    • Alicisindan.Listing
  • public class Listing
extends java.lang.Object
    Listing class. Includes every Listing getter and setter methods. You can create and save a Listing by giving its credentials to the server. All getters and setters are non-static.

      • Listing

        public Listing​(java.lang.String ownerid,
               java.lang.String type,
               java.lang.String title,
               java.lang.String description,
               java.lang.String price,
               java.lang.String category,
               java.lang.String location,
               java.lang.String condition,
               java.lang.String brand)
        Secondary constructor, for creating the Listing object BEFORE REGISTERATION. Image and tags are not stored within the Listing object!
        Parameters:
        ownerid - ID number of the listing's owner.
        type - Listing type. CAN BE "sell" OR "buy"
        title - Listing title.
        description - Listing description.
        price - Listing price.
        category - Listing category.
        location - Listing location.
        condition - Listing's condition.
        brand - Listing's brand.

    • Method Detail

      • addListing

        public void addListing​(java.lang.String userId,
                       java.lang.String userPassword)
                throws java.lang.Exception
        Registers a Listing object to the database. CREATES A NEW ID INDEPENDENT ON WHATEVER ID THE CURRENT OBJECT HAS!! THEREFORE, CAN'T BE USED TO MAKE CHANGES TO AN EXISTING LISTING!! Doesn't upload images!
        Parameters:
        userId - of owner of the listing
        userPassword - of owner of the listing
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - when socket returns unexpected response.

      • findListings

        public static Listing[] findListings​(java.lang.String ownerID,
                                     java.lang.String categories,
                                     java.lang.String exactTitle,
                                     java.lang.String searchedTitle,
                                     java.lang.String type,
                                     java.lang.String condition,
                                     java.lang.String minPrice,
                                     java.lang.String maxPrice,
                                     java.lang.String location,
                                     java.lang.String order,
                                     java.lang.String offset,
                                     java.lang.String limit)
                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Searches for Listing objects in database. For any parameter, use the null keywoard for no filter.
        Parameters:
        ownerID - to filter for.
        categories - to filter for. Seperate multiple categories with ";".
        exactTitle - to filter for.
        searchedTitle - to filter for. Will return listings with similar titles too. Don't use both exactTitle and searchedTitle parameters!
        type - to filter for. Listing.SELL or Listing.BUY
        condition - to filter for.
        minPrice - to filter for. Integer in String format is needed.
        maxPrice - to filter for. Integer in String format is needed.
        location - to filter for.
        order - to get listings with. POSSIBLE INPUTS: Listing.NEWESTFIRST, Listing.OLDESTFIRST, Listing.CHEAPFIRST, Listing.EXPENSIVEFIRST
        offset - Number of listings to skip while getting listings.
        limit - Number of listigns to get.
        Returns:
        Array of Listing objects.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - when socket returns unexpected response.
